./setup.sh

-----------------------------
If MACOS

Check .bash_profile for outdated links


Also, in iterm2 > Preferences > Profiles > General > Command > Command : ssh -Y admin > Working Directory > Reuse previous session
         iterm2 > Preferences > Advanced > Tabs > Add new tab at the end of tab bar

OR with mosh:
Install mosh in both client and server
Also, in iterm2 > Preferences > Profiles > General > Command > Login Shell:/usr/local/bin/mosh admin > Working Directory > Reuse previous session
iterm2 > Preferences > Selection > Applications in terminal may access clipboard

optional: if need to ssh to an admin machine:
if using custom.sh, need to setup $REMOTE_NAME

-----------------------------
If Windows
Use Cygwin
Script will change home directory of cygwin, do this before running
    echo -e 'db_home:  /%H/cygwin' >> /etc/nsswitch.conf
Restart Cygwin

In tmux, hold Shift + drag mouse to copy to windows clipboard

Visual Studio code
Vim extension, files > systems > settings, search for "vim clipboard", need to reopen file

-----------------------------

For Python:
    virtualenv

For Ruby:
    rvm
    bundler
    pgp

-----------------------------

ctags -Ra /usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/*
cd /usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/ && ctags -R * && ctags -Ra /usr/lib/python2.7/
